abstract:
In this paper we introduce and develop the method of compression of points in space. We introduce the notion of the mass, the rank, the entropy, the cover and the energy of compression. We leverage this method to prove some class of inequalities related to Diophantine equations. In particular, we show that for each $L<n-1$ and for each $K>n-1$, there exist some $(x_1,x_2,\ldots,x_n)\in \mathbb{N}^n$ with $x_i
eq x_j$ for all $1\leq i<j\leq n$ such that  egin{align} rac{1}{K^{n}}\ll \prod \limits_{j=1}^{n} rac{1}{x_j}\ll  rac{\log ( rac{n}{L})}{nL^{n-1}}
